{"key":"processedPost-14573075","value":{"id":14573075,"first":14571933,"last":14573219,"when":1307450771,"utime":"06/07/11 03:46 PM","cleanedPost":"You're confused over that video because he didn't know what the fuck he's talking about.&nbsp; The blatant mistakes have been brought up many times over the last year.<br />Spawn is normally your grains or brf cakes, etc., that you use to inoculate your bulk substrate.&nbsp; A bulk substrate is material such as straw, manure, coir, etc.<br />A casing layer is a non-nutritious material that is placed over the bulk substrate, but is not necessary with cubensis and most other species as well.&nbsp; There's been a lot of misinformation posted on this board over the years too, where people refer to their 'casing' as if it were a name for 'the tray I grow mushrooms in' but this is incorrect.<br />RR"}}